title: Audio jack keeps stopping (USB Debugging mode no longer helps) Weird green substance in port?
content:
I've had the on going issues of my audio jack not working (brought a new one, have the usb debugging mode activated) and only recently my audio is no longer coming through my headphones and will just jump to the speaker's.

I've unplugged my headphones today and noticed there's a green substance in the audio jack that was not there a few days ago. 

Any one able to suggest what to do?
